# Testing Minimum Bar

- Critical flows require at least one automated smoke test before merge.
- Critical flows include: auth, onboarding completion, listing creation, chat send/receive.
- Every bug fix should add a regression test when practical.
- Prefer small, deterministic tests over broad flaky integration tests.
- Do not mark launch-critical work complete without a reproducible verification path.
- If tests are deferred, record risk and a dated follow-up task explicitly.
